Use AI Models

Einstein Studio is your home base for AI in Data Cloud. Augment your business intelligence with AI to identify, surface, and visualize inferences in your Data Cloud data. AI is integrated into your Data Cloud environment so that you can quickly operationalize generative models, predictions, and improvements with clicks, not code.

Einstein Studio Glossary
Familiarize yourself with terminology that is commonly associated with Einstein Studio.
Create, Connect, and Activate Models
Create your own predictive models with clicks, not code. Establish connections to bring in generative and predictive AI from models outside of Salesforce. Then, activate models to use the inferences and insights revealed in your data.
Activate Your Model
After saving your predictive model settings, the model is ready for activation. To consume predictions, you must first activate the model.
Manage Models
After creating a predictive model, you can edit to update your settings or delete it if it’s no longer needed.
Utilize Model Output
After a model is activated, you can use it to get predicted outcomes and suggested improvements in different ways. You can use connected models in Flow Builder and query them directly. Use created and connected models in prediction jobs, and predict nodes. Also, retrieve predictions and improvements programmatically via REST or Apex.
